===Etymology===
The noun is from {{etyl|enm|en}} {{m|enm|doute}}, from {{etyl|xno|en}} and {{etyl|fro|en}} {{m|fro|doute}}, from {{etyl|la|en}} {{m|la|dubita}}. The modern spelling is probably under the influence of {{etyl|frm|en}} {{m|frm|doubte}}.

The verb is from {{etyl|enm|en}} {{m|enm|douten}}, from {{etyl|xno|en}} {{m|fro|douter}}, from {{etyl|fro|en}} {{m|fro|douter}}, from {{etyl|la|en}} {{m|la|dubitō}}, from the noun. Replaced {{etyl|enm|-}} {{m|enm|tweonien||to doubt}} (from {{etyl|ang|-}} {{m|ang|twēonian}}, compare {{etyl|ang|-}} {{m|ang|twēo||doubt, duplicity}}). The modern spelling is probably under the influence of {{etyl|frm|en}} {{m|frm|doubter}}.

